HEADWORD: Exsiccate
<hw>Ex"sic*cate</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Exsiccated</conjf><pr>(?)</pr>;
<pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Exsiccating</conjf>.]</vmorph>
<ety>[L. <ets>exsiccatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>exsiccare</ets> to dry up;
<ets>ex</ets> out + <ets>siccare</ets> to make dry, <ets>siccus</ets>
dry.]</ety> <def>To exhaust or evaporate moisture from; to dry up.</def>
<rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

